1
00:00:06,583 --> 00:00:10,000
Katara: WATER...

2
00:00:10,041 --> 00:00:11,583
EARTH...

3
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:14,000
FIRE...

4
00:00:14,041 --> 00:00:16,166
AIR.

5
00:00:16,208 --> 00:00:20,542
LONG AGO, THE 4 NATIONS
LIVED TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

6
00:00:20,583 --> 00:00:24,125
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

7
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:27,750
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL 4 ELEMENTS,

8
00:00:27,792 --> 00:00:29,000
COULD STOP THEM.

9
00:00:29,041 --> 00:00:30,500
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST,

10
00:00:30,542 --> 00:00:31,667
HE VANISHED.

11
00:00:31,709 --> 00:00:33,834
100 YEARS PASSED,

12
00:00:33,875 --> 00:00:35,709
AND MY BROTHER AND I
DISCOVERED THE NEW AVATAR--

13
00:00:35,750 --> 00:00:38,083
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

14
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:39,542
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS ARE GREAT,

15
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:43,125
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

16
00:00:43,166 --> 00:00:44,166
Aang: OOF.

17
00:00:44,208 --> 00:00:47,500
BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

18
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:58,500
I DISCOVERED A HIDDEN LIBRARY.

19
00:00:58,542 --> 00:01:01,500
I TORE THROUGH
SCROLL AFTER SCROLL.

20
00:01:04,709 --> 00:01:06,375
Toph: YOU DID IT!

21
00:01:06,417 --> 00:01:07,792
YOU'RE AN EARTHBENDER.

22
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:11,709
SOZEN'S COMET WILL RETURN
BY THE END OF THE SUMMER.

23
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:15,583
AND FIRE LORD OZAI WILL USE
ITS POWER TO FINISH THE WAR

24
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:17,458
ONCE AND FOR ALL.

25
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:19,875
YOU MUST DEFEAT THE FIRE LORD

26
00:01:19,917 --> 00:01:21,917
BEFORE THE COMET ARRIVES.

27
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:33,125
Sokka:
WHAT'S OUT HERE?

28
00:01:33,166 --> 00:01:35,583
Toph: A LOT,
ACTUALLY. THERE'S
HUNDREDS OF LITTLE--

29
00:01:35,625 --> 00:01:37,583
SHH! I KNOW YOU
CAN SEE UNDERGROUND,

30
00:01:37,625 --> 00:01:39,542
BUT DON'T RUIN THE SURPRISE.

31
00:01:39,583 --> 00:01:40,959
JUST WATCH.

32
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,083
♪♪

33
00:01:42,125 --> 00:01:43,333
♪ EH ♪

34
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:45,166
HA HA! YEAH!

35
00:01:45,208 --> 00:01:46,333
♪♪

36
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:47,542
♪ EH! ♪

37
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,250
I'M PUTTING
AN ORCHESTRA TOGETHER.

38
00:01:49,291 --> 00:01:51,208
ORCHESTRA, HUH? WELL...

39
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,125
♪ LA-DI-DA ♪

40
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:55,208
♪ LAAH ♪
♪ DIIH ♪
♪ DAAH ♪

41
00:01:57,792 --> 00:01:58,750
♪♪
♪♪

42
00:01:58,792 --> 00:01:59,917
♪ EH ♪

43
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:00,917
♪ EH! ♪

44
00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:01,917
♪ EH! ♪

45
00:02:01,959 --> 00:02:04,625
♪ EH ♪

46
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:06,041
THIS IS GREAT AND ALL,

47
00:02:06,083 --> 00:02:07,792
BUT DON'T WE HAVE MORE
IMPORTANT THINGS
TO WORRY ABOUT?

48
00:02:07,834 --> 00:02:09,750
WE SHOULD
BE MAKING PLANS.

49
00:02:09,792 --> 00:02:11,500
WE DID MAKE PLANS.

50
00:02:11,542 --> 00:02:13,375
WE'RE ALL PICKING
MINI-VACATIONS.

51
00:02:13,417 --> 00:02:15,375
THERE'S NO TIME
FOR VACATIONS.

52
00:02:15,417 --> 00:02:17,750
I'M LEARNING THE ELEMENTS
AS FAST AS I CAN.

53
00:02:17,792 --> 00:02:20,250
I PRACTICE HARD EVERY DAY
WITH TOPH AND KATARA.

54
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:22,709
I'VE BEEN TRAINING
MY ARROW OFF.

55
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:26,083
YEAH. WHAT'S WRONG
WITH HAVING A LITTLE
FUN IN OUR DOWNTIME?

56
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:28,375
EVEN IF YOU DO MASTER
ALL OF THE ELEMENTS,
THEN WHAT?

57
00:02:28,417 --> 00:02:30,875
IT'S NOT LIKE WE HAVE
A MAP OF THE FIRE NATION.

58
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:33,625
SHOULD WE JUST HEAD WEST
UNTIL WE REACH
THE FIRE LORD'S HOUSE?

59
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:36,166
KNOCK, KNOCK!
HELLO, FIRE LORD!
ANYBODY HOME?

60
00:02:36,208 --> 00:02:37,542
I DON'T THINK SO.

61
00:02:37,583 --> 00:02:39,542
WE NEED SOME INTELLIGENCE
IF WE'RE GONNA WIN THIS WAR.

62
00:02:39,583 --> 00:02:40,500
♪♪
♪♪

63
00:02:40,542 --> 00:02:42,875
♪ LAAH ♪

64
00:02:42,917 --> 00:02:44,834
HEE HEE! ALL RIGHT.
WE'LL FINISH
OUR VACATIONS.

65
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:47,750
AND THEN WE'LL
LOOK FOR SOKKA'S
INTELLIGENCE.

66
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,750
Aang: YOUR TURN, KATARA.

67
00:02:49,792 --> 00:02:51,625
WHERE WOULD YOU
LIKE TO GO ON
YOUR MINI-VACATION?

68
00:02:51,667 --> 00:02:54,291
HOW ABOUT
THE MISTY PALMS
OASIS?

69
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,875
THAT SOUNDS
REFRESHING.

70
00:02:55,917 --> 00:02:57,542
OH, YEAH, I'VE BEEN THERE.

71
00:02:57,583 --> 00:02:58,709
IT'S A PRISTINE
NATURAL ICE GROUND.

72
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:01,375
AND I DON'T USUALLY
USE THE WORD "PRISTINE."

73
00:03:01,417 --> 00:03:03,333
IT'S ONE OF
NATURE'S WONDERS.

74
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:05,583
[SOUNDTRACK MUSIC
SLOWS DOWN]

75
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:08,291
MUST HAVE CHANGED
OWNERSHIP SINCE
I WAS HERE.

76
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:10,542
HEH HEH.

77
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:21,625
PTOOEY!

78
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:24,667
[GROWLING]

79
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:32,125
[SNORING]

80
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:34,041
ONE MANGO, PLEASE.

81
00:03:47,959 --> 00:03:49,542
I DON'T SEE ANYTHING WRONG

82
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:51,875
WITH HAVING ONE OF THOSE
FRUITY BEVERAGES

83
00:03:51,917 --> 00:03:54,333
WHILE WE PLAN OUR STRATEGY.

84
00:03:54,375 --> 00:03:56,041
EXCUSE ME.

85
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:01,458
NO WORRIES.
I CLEAN UP EASY.

86
00:04:02,792 --> 00:04:04,083
YOU'RE
A LIVING RELIC.

87
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:06,458
THANKS. I TRY.

88
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:09,625
AN AIR NOMAD RIGHT
FRONT OF ME.

89
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:11,458
PROFESSOR ZEI,
HEAD OF ANTHROPOLOGY

90
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,250
AT BA SING SE
UNIVERSITY.

91
00:04:13,291 --> 00:04:14,375
TELL ME...

92
00:04:14,417 --> 00:04:17,583
WHICH OF THE
AIR TEMPLES DO
YOU HAIL FROM?

93
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:18,917
THE SOUTHERN TEMPLE.

94
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:21,792
OH, SPLENDID!
NOW, TELL ME,

95
00:04:21,834 --> 00:04:24,375
WHAT WAS THE PRIMARY
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT
OF YOUR PEOPLE?

96
00:04:24,417 --> 00:04:28,583
UH, ARE FRUIT PIES
AN AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT?

97
00:04:28,625 --> 00:04:31,917
OH! TRULY
FASCINATING. THAT'S
ONE FOR THE JOURNAL.

98
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:35,333
Sokka: SO, PROFESSOR,
YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
A WELL-TRAVELED GUY.

99
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,458
DO YOU HAVE A MORE
CURRENT MAP?

100
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,041
OURS SEEMS TO BE
A LITTLE DATED.

101
00:04:38,083 --> 00:04:40,542
CERTAINLY.

102
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:47,834
WHAT? NO FIRE NATION?
DOESN'T ANYBODY HAVE
A GOOD MAP OF THAT PLACE?

103
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:49,917
Katara: YOU'VE MADE A LOT
OF TRIPS INTO THE DESERT.

104
00:04:49,959 --> 00:04:51,959
Zei: ALL IN VAIN,
I'M AFRAID.

105
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,917
I'VE FOUND LOST
CIVILIZATIONS ALL OVER
THE EARTH KINGDOM,

106
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:58,959
BUT I HAVEN'T
MANAGED TO FIND
THE CROWN JEWEL--

107
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,834
WAN-CHI TONG'S LIBRARY.

108
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:04,917
YOU'VE SPENT YEARS
WALKING THROUGH
THE DESERT TO FIND

109
00:05:04,959 --> 00:05:06,291
SOME GUY'S LIBRARY?

110
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:10,583
THIS LIBRARY IS MORE
VALUABLE THAN GOLD,
LITTLE LADY.

111
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:11,875
IT IS SAID TO
CONTAIN A VAST
COLLECTION

112
00:05:11,917 --> 00:05:14,083
OF KNOWLEDGE.

113
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:15,709
AND KNOWLEDGE...

114
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,291
IS PRICELESS.

115
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,417
[DEADPAN]
HMM. SOUNDS
LIKE GOOD TIMES.

116
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:21,625
OH, IT IS.
ACCORDING TO
LEGEND,

117
00:05:21,667 --> 00:05:24,834
IT WAS BUILT
BY THE GREAT
KNOWLEDGE SPIRIT

118
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:27,458
WAN-CHI TONG
WITH THE HELP

119
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,667
OF HIS
FOXY KNOWLEDGE
SEEKERS.

120
00:05:29,709 --> 00:05:32,917
OH, SO THIS SPIRIT
HAS ATTRACTIVE
ASSISTANTS, HUH?

121
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:35,250
I THINK HE MEANS
THEY LOOK LIKE
ACTUAL FOXES, SOKKA.

122
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:37,083
Zei: YOU'RE BOTH RIGHT.

123
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:38,583
HANDSOME LITTLE CREATURES.

124
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:41,000
WAN-CHI TONG AND HIS
KNOWLEDGE SEEKERS

125
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,417
COLLECTED BOOKS FROM
ALL OVER THE WORLD

126
00:05:43,458 --> 00:05:46,291
AND PUT THEM ON DISPLAY
FOR MANKIND TO READ

127
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,166
SO THAT WE MIGHT
BETTER OURSELVES.

128
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:49,709
IF THIS PLACE HAS BOOKS
FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD,

129
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,625
DO YOU THINK THEY'VE GOT
INFO ON THE FIRE NATION?

130
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:52,583
A MAP MAYBE?

131
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:54,375
I WOULDN'T KNOW.

132
00:05:54,417 --> 00:05:56,959
BUT IF SUCH
A THING EXISTS,

133
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,500
IT'S IN
WAN-CHI TONG'S
LIBRARY.

134
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:04,542
THEN IT'S SETTLED. AANG,
I DO BELIEVE IT'S MY TURN.

135
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:07,500
I'D LIKE TO SPEND MY VACATION
AT THE LIBRARY!

136
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:12,583
UH, HEY, WHAT ABOUT ME?
WHEN DO I GET TO PICK?

137
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,041
Sokka: YOU'VE GOT TO WORK
HERE A LITTLE LONGER

138
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:15,750
BEFORE YOU'RE QUALIFIED
FOR VACATION TIME.

139
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:17,250
HMPH.

140
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:18,125
OF COURSE, THERE'S THE MATTER

141
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:19,500
OF FINDING IT.

142
00:06:19,542 --> 00:06:21,542
I'VE MADE SEVERAL TRIPS
INTO THE ZI HUANG DESERT

143
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,625
AND ALMOST DIED EACH TIME.

144
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:26,917
I'M AFRAID THAT DESERT'S
IMPOSSIBLE TO CROSS.

145
00:06:26,959 --> 00:06:30,792
PROFESSOR, WOULD
YOU LIKE TO SEE
OUR SKY BISON?

146
00:06:30,834 --> 00:06:33,875
A SKY BISON? YOU
ACTUALLY HAVE ONE?!

147
00:06:33,917 --> 00:06:36,291
[GROWLING]

148
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:39,333
SANDBENDERS, SHOO!
AWAY FROM THE BISON!

149
00:07:00,792 --> 00:07:03,875
TELL ME, SKY BISON,
ARE YOU THE LAST
OF YOUR BREED?

150
00:07:03,917 --> 00:07:08,792
OH, DELIGHTFUL! I
ONLY WISH I SPOKE
HIS TONGUE.

151
00:07:08,834 --> 00:07:12,917
OH, THE STORIES
THIS BEAST
COULD TELL.

152
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:14,458
SHUSH,
CHATTY MONKEY.

153
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:16,834
WOW. IT SHOULDN'T BE
TOO HARD

154
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:18,166
TO FIND A PLACE LIKE THIS

155
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:19,458
OUT HERE.

156
00:07:23,417 --> 00:07:25,000
AH! DOES THIS PLACE
EVEN EXIST?

157
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:27,917
SOME SAY IT DOESN'T.

158
00:07:27,959 --> 00:07:30,125
SHOULDN'T YOU
HAVE MENTIONED
THAT BEFORE?

159
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:31,792
GRR!

160
00:07:36,834 --> 00:07:38,375
THERE IT IS!

161
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:45,333
THAT'S WHAT IT
WILL SOUND LIKE WHEN
ONE OF YOU SPOTS IT.

162
00:07:47,709 --> 00:07:48,625
[APPA GROWLING]

163
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:51,625
IT SHOULDN'T
BE THIS HARD
TO SPOT

164
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:53,583
A GIANT ORNATE
BUILDING
FROM THE AIR.

165
00:07:57,041 --> 00:07:58,583
DOWN THERE. WHAT'S THAT?

166
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:07,375
FORGET IT. IT'S
OBVIOUSLY NOT WHAT
WE'RE LOOKING FOR.

167
00:08:07,417 --> 00:08:09,333
THE BUILDING IN THIS
DRAWING IS ENORMOUS.

168
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,792
WHAT KIND OF ANIMAL
IS THAT?

169
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:25,750
Zei: I THINK THAT WAS ONE
OF THE KNOWLEDGE SEEKERS.

170
00:08:25,792 --> 00:08:28,333
OH, WE MUST BE CLOSE
TO THE LIBRARY.

171
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:30,709
NO. THIS
IS THE LIBRARY.
LOOK!

172
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:35,250
IT'S COMPLETELY
BURIED.

173
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:45,500
Zei: THE LIBRARY IS BURIED?!

174
00:08:45,542 --> 00:08:48,208
MY LIFE'S AMBITION IS
NOW FULL OF SAND.

175
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:50,875
WELL, TIME TO START
EXCAVATING.

176
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:56,250
ACTUALLY, THAT WON'T
BE NECESSARY.

177
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,500
THE INSIDE SEEMS TO BE
COMPLETELY INTACT.

178
00:08:58,542 --> 00:09:00,750
AND IT'S HUGE.

179
00:09:00,792 --> 00:09:02,959
Sokka: THAT FOX THINGY
WENT IN THROUGH A WINDOW.

180
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,458
I SAY WE CLIMB UP THERE
AND GIVE IT A LOOK.

181
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,917
I SAY YOU GUYS
GO AHEAD WITHOUT ME.

182
00:09:07,959 --> 00:09:08,750
YOU'VE GOT SOMETHING
AGAINST LIBRARIES?

183
00:09:08,792 --> 00:09:11,083
I'VE HELD BOOKS
BEFORE.

184
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:13,083
AND I GOT
TO TELL YOU,

185
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:15,291
THEY DON'T EXACTLY
DO IT FOR ME.

186
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:18,041
OH, RIGHT. SORRY.

187
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:20,291
LET ME KNOW IF THEY HAVE
SOMETHING YOU CAN LISTEN TO.

188
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:29,375
DON'T WORRY, BUDDY.
I'M NOT MAKING YOU GO
UNDERGROUND EVER AGAIN.

189
00:09:29,417 --> 00:09:30,959
YOU CAN STAY
OUT HERE WITH TOPH.

190
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:38,583
WHAT'S UP?

191
00:09:45,709 --> 00:09:46,875
[CHATTERS]

192
00:09:48,542 --> 00:09:51,083
Zei: OH, IT'S BREATHTAKING.

193
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:53,458
THE SPIRIT SPARED
NO EXPENSE IN
DESIGNING THIS PLACE.

194
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,000
LOOK AT THOSE
BEAUTIFUL BUTTRESSES.

195
00:09:56,041 --> 00:09:57,500
HEE HEE!
HEE HEE!

196
00:09:57,542 --> 00:09:58,917
Zei: WHAT'S
FUNNY?

197
00:09:58,959 --> 00:10:01,125
NOTHING. WE JUST
LIKE ARCHITECTURE.

198
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:02,917
AS DO I.

199
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:06,583
MY WORD!

200
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:11,333
THE EXQUISITE MOSAIC
HANDIWORK OF THIS
TILE-RENDERED AVIAN SYMBOL--

201
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:14,709
EH, NICE OWL.

202
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,834
[RUSTLING]

203
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:18,625
[CHATTERING]

204
00:10:29,917 --> 00:10:32,834
I KNOW YOU'RE
BACK THERE.

205
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:36,875
HELLO!

206
00:10:36,917 --> 00:10:39,166
I'M PROFESSOR ZEI,
HEAD OF ANTHROPOLOGY

207
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:41,083
AT BA SING SE
UNIVERSITY.

208
00:10:41,125 --> 00:10:44,542
YOU SHOULD LEAVE
THE WAY YOU CAME

209
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:48,083
UNLESS YOU WANT
TO BECOME A STUFFED HEAD
OF ANTHROPOLOGY.

210
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:49,000
[SPEAKING GIBBERISH]

211
00:10:49,041 --> 00:10:51,125
Sokka: ARE YOU THE SPIRIT

212
00:10:51,166 --> 00:10:53,208
WHO BROUGHT THIS LIBRARY
TO THE PHYSICAL WORLD?

213
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:58,083
INDEED. I AM WAN-CHI TONG,
HE WHO KNOWS 10,000 THINGS.

214
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:00,000
AND YOU ARE
OBVIOUSLY HUMANS,

215
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:03,625
WHICH, BY THE WAY,
ARE NO LONGER
PERMITTED IN MY STUDY.

216
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:05,041
Aang: WHAT
DO YOU HAVE
AGAINST HUMANS?

217
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:08,125
HMM. HUMANS
ONLY BOTHER
LEARNING THINGS

218
00:11:08,166 --> 00:11:11,125
TO GET THE EDGE
ON OTHER HUMANS,

219
00:11:11,166 --> 00:11:13,750
LIKE THAT FIREBENDER
WHO CAME TO THIS PLACE
A FEW YEARS AGO,

220
00:11:13,792 --> 00:11:17,083
LOOKING TO DESTROY
HIS ENEMY.

221
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:20,291
SO WHO ARE YOU
TRYING TO DESTROY?

222
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:24,291
WHAT? NO, NO,
NO DESTROYING.
WE'RE NOT INTO THAT.

223
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,125
Wan-Chi Tong: THEN WHY
HAVE YOU COME HERE?

224
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:30,500
UM, KNOWLEDGE FOR
KNOWLEDGE'S SAKE.

225
00:11:30,542 --> 00:11:35,208
IF YOU'RE GOING TO LIE
TO AN ALL-KNOWING
SPIRIT BEING,

226
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:37,917
YOU SHOULD AT LEAST
PUT SOME EFFORT INTO IT.

227
00:11:37,959 --> 00:11:40,667
I'M NOT LYING!
I'M HERE WITH
THE AVATAR,

228
00:11:40,709 --> 00:11:42,083
AND HE'S THE
BRIDGE BETWEEN
OUR WORLDS.

229
00:11:42,125 --> 00:11:43,917
HE'LL VOUCH
FOR ME.

230
00:11:43,959 --> 00:11:45,000
OW!

231
00:11:45,041 --> 00:11:47,875
UH, YEAH. I'LL VOUCH.

232
00:11:47,917 --> 00:11:51,125
WE WILL NOT ABUSE
THE KNOWLEDGE IN YOUR
LIBRARY, GOOD SPIRIT.

233
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:52,709
YOU HAVE MY WORD.

234
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:58,417
HMM. VERY WELL.
I'LL LET YOU PERUSE
MY VAST COLLECTION

235
00:11:58,458 --> 00:12:00,291
ON ONE CONDITION--

236
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:02,500
TO PROVE YOUR WORTH
AS SCHOLARS,

237
00:12:02,542 --> 00:12:06,583
YOU HAVE TO CONTRIBUTE
SOME WORTHWHILE KNOWLEDGE.

238
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:10,625
PLEASE ACCEPT THIS
TOME AS A DONATION
TO YOUR LIBRARY.

239
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:13,625
FIRST EDITION.
VERY NICE.

240
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:19,709
I HAVE AN AUTHENTIC
WATERBENDING SCROLL.

241
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:23,709
OH, THESE ILLUSTRATIONS
ARE QUITE STYLISH.

242
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:28,041
UH, OH! I KNOW.

243
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:29,583
HA!

244
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:33,500
I SUPPOSE THAT COUNTS.

245
00:12:33,542 --> 00:12:36,458
OH, GREAT SPIRIT,
CHECK THIS OUT.

246
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:39,166
TA-DA!

247
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:40,875
IT'S A SPECIAL KNOT.

248
00:12:40,917 --> 00:12:42,458
THAT COUNTS
AS KNOWLEDGE.

249
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:45,041
YOU'RE NOT
VERY BRIGHT, ARE YOU?

250
00:12:47,041 --> 00:12:48,959
ENJOY THE LIBRARY.

251
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,959
BRIGHT ENOUGH TO FOOL YOU.

252
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:04,542
SO, DO YOU LIKE FLYING?

253
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:09,083
OF COURSE, I'M MORE
COMFORTABLE ON
THE GROUND

254
00:13:09,125 --> 00:13:10,834
WHERE I CAN SEE.

255
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:13,125
WELL, I DON'T SEE
THE WAY YOU DO.

256
00:13:13,166 --> 00:13:14,875
I FEEL
THE VIBRATIONS
IN THE GROUND

257
00:13:14,917 --> 00:13:16,375
WITH MY FEET.

258
00:13:16,417 --> 00:13:19,333
BUT THIS SAND IS
SO LOOSE AND SHIFTY,

259
00:13:19,375 --> 00:13:22,125
IT MAKES EVERYTHING
LOOK FUZZY.

260
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:23,291
[GROWLS]

261
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:25,041
NOT THAT THERE'S
ANYTHING WRONG
WITH FUZZY.

262
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:38,625
HEY! LOOK AT THESE
WEIRD LION-TURTLE THINGS.

263
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:40,208
AH, I'VE SEEN
WEIRDER.

264
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,834
AANG, DID YOU KNOW
IN A PAST LIFE,

265
00:13:41,875 --> 00:13:43,875
YOU WERE LEFT-HANDED?

266
00:13:43,917 --> 00:13:46,208
I ALWAYS KNEW
I WAS SPECIAL.

267
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:59,000
"THE DARKEST DAY
IN FIRE NATION HISTORY."

268
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:01,792
IT'S GOT A DATE AT THE TOP,

269
00:14:01,834 --> 00:14:03,125
BUT IT DOESN'T
SAY ANYTHING ELSE.

270
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:11,250
SOKKA, WHERE ARE
YOU GOING?

271
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,834
I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE FIRE NATION

272
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:15,959
ON THEIR DARKEST DAY.
THIS COULD BE PROMISING.

273
00:14:17,959 --> 00:14:18,834
THE INFORMATION
ON THE FIRE NATION

274
00:14:18,875 --> 00:14:21,500
SHOULD BE RIGHT UP HERE.

275
00:14:23,291 --> 00:14:23,917
Aang: FIREBENDERS.

276
00:14:23,959 --> 00:14:25,250
Katara: THEY DESTROYED

277
00:14:25,291 --> 00:14:27,709
EVERYTHING HAVING TO DO
WITH THE FIRE NATION.

278
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:29,667
THAT'S SO UNFAIR!

279
00:14:29,709 --> 00:14:33,208
JUST WHEN I THINK
I'M ONE STEP AHEAD OF
THE FIRE NATION,

280
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:36,208
IT TURNS OUT THEY BEAT
US HERE A LONG TIME AGO.

281
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,500
I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED ON
THE DARKEST DAY.

282
00:14:38,542 --> 00:14:41,000
[WHIMPERING]

283
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:44,625
HELLO,
LITTLE WEIRD FOX GUY.

284
00:14:46,583 --> 00:14:49,625
Zei: IT SEEMS IT'S
TRYING TO ASSIST YOU.

285
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:53,041
UM, SURE. I GUESS I'LL
FOLLOW YOU.

286
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:23,291
THIS ROOM IS A TRUE MARVEL,
A MECHANICAL WONDER.

287
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:27,834
IT'S A PLANETARIUM
THAT SHOWS
THE HEAVENS MOVING.

288
00:15:30,166 --> 00:15:33,875
Sokka: THIS IS BEAUTIFUL,
BUT HOW IS IT HELPFUL?

289
00:15:33,917 --> 00:15:36,625
MAYBE THESE DIALS
REPRESENT DATES AND TIMES.

290
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:40,125
SOKKA, TRY ENTERING
THAT DATE FROM THAT
PARCHMENT YOU TOOK.

291
00:15:40,166 --> 00:15:45,375
SHH! KATARA, NOT
IN FRONT OF THE FOX.
HE'S WITH THE OWL.

292
00:15:45,417 --> 00:15:46,125
[WHIMPERS]

293
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,917
WOW! I GOT TO HAND
IT TO YOU, SOKKA,

294
00:16:06,959 --> 00:16:09,125
YOU PICKED
THE BEST MINI-VACATION
FOR SURE.

295
00:16:13,834 --> 00:16:16,000
Katara: HEY, WAIT.
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE SUN?

296
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:18,542
GREAT. YOU MUST
HAVE BROKEN IT.

297
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:21,875
IT'S NOT BROKEN.

298
00:16:21,917 --> 00:16:26,041
THE SUN IS BEHIND THE MOON.
IT'S A SOLAR ECLIPSE.

299
00:16:26,083 --> 00:16:28,959
IT'S LITERALLY THE DARKEST
DAY IN FIRE NATION HISTORY.

300
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:32,000
NOW I GET IT.
SOMETHING AWFUL HAPPENED
ON THAT DAY.

301
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:33,667
I DON'T KNOW WHAT,
BUT I DO KNOW WHY.

302
00:16:33,709 --> 00:16:37,625
FIREBENDERS LOSE
THEIR BENDING DURING
A SOLAR ECLIPSE. SORRY.

303
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:39,083
THAT
MAKES SENSE.

304
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:42,125
I MEAN, THINK OF
WHAT THE LUNAR
ECLIPSE

305
00:16:42,166 --> 00:16:43,667
AT THE NORTH POLE
DID TO
THE WATERBENDERS.

306
00:16:43,709 --> 00:16:45,083
THIS IS HUGE.

307
00:16:45,125 --> 00:16:47,542
[FOX WHIMPERS]

308
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:49,917
FINE. YOU EARNED IT.

309
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:53,458
WE'VE GOT TO GET
THIS INFORMATION
TO THE EARTH KING

310
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,792
AT BA SING SE.

311
00:16:54,834 --> 00:16:57,250
WE'LL WAIT FOR
THE NEXT ECLIPSE.

312
00:16:57,291 --> 00:16:59,583
THEN WE'LL INVADE
THE FIRE NATION WHEN
THEY'RE TOTALLY HELPLESS.

313
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:02,709
THE FIRE LORD IS GOING DOWN!

314
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:05,542
MORTALS ARE SO
PREDICTABLE

315
00:17:05,583 --> 00:17:07,667
AND SUCH
TERRIBLE LIARS.

316
00:17:07,709 --> 00:17:09,083
[SOKKA GULPS]

317
00:17:13,583 --> 00:17:16,083
YOU BETRAYED MY TRUST.

318
00:17:16,125 --> 00:17:17,458
FROM THE BEGINNING,
YOU INTENDED TO MISUSE
THIS KNOWLEDGE

319
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:20,500
FOR EVIL PURPOSES.

320
00:17:20,542 --> 00:17:24,667
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
IF ANYONE'S EVIL,
IT'S THE FIRE NATION.

321
00:17:24,709 --> 00:17:25,959
YOU SAW WHAT THEY DID
TO YOUR LIBRARY.

322
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,208
THEY'RE DESTRUCTIVE
AND DANGEROUS.

323
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:30,125
WE NEED
THIS INFORMATION.

324
00:17:30,166 --> 00:17:32,250
YOU THINK YOU'RE
THE FIRST PERSON
TO BELIEVE

325
00:17:32,291 --> 00:17:33,959
THEIR WAR WAS JUSTIFIED?

326
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,667
COUNTLESS OTHERS BEFORE
YOU HAVE COME HERE,

327
00:17:36,709 --> 00:17:39,959
SEEKING WEAPONS
OR WEAKNESSES OR
BATTLE STRATEGIES.

328
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,667
WE HAD NO CHOICE.
PLEASE. WE'RE JUST
DESPERATE TO PROTECT

329
00:17:42,709 --> 00:17:44,083
THE PEOPLE WE LOVE.

330
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:47,917
AND NOW I AM GOING
TO PROTECT WHAT I LOVE.

331
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:53,625
Aang: WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

332
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:59,166
I'M TAKING
MY KNOWLEDGE BACK. NO ONE
WILL EVER ABUSE IT AGAIN.

333
00:17:59,208 --> 00:18:02,125
HE'S SINKING THE BUILDING.
WE'VE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE!

334
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:06,291
I'M AFRAID
I CAN'T ALLOW THAT.
YOU ALREADY KNOW TOO MUCH.

335
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:07,458
AAH!
AAH!

336
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,834
[KIDS SCREAMING]

337
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,750
[GROWLS]

338
00:18:16,792 --> 00:18:19,458
I ALREADY TOLD YOU.
I DON'T WANT TO SNUGGLE.

339
00:18:23,959 --> 00:18:27,792
LIBRARY'S SINKING.
LIBRARY'S SINKING!

340
00:18:27,834 --> 00:18:30,083
HYAH!

341
00:18:37,417 --> 00:18:38,667
[YELLS]

342
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:56,625
AAH!

343
00:18:56,667 --> 00:18:59,959
GREAT KNOWLEDGE
SPIRIT, I BEG YOU,

344
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:06,000
DO NOT DESTROY YOUR
VAST COLLECTION OF
PRICELESS TOMES.

345
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:07,041
AAH!

346
00:19:14,792 --> 00:19:17,667
WE'VE GOT TO GET BACK
TO THE SURFACE.

347
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:20,792
SOKKA, LET'S GO.

348
00:19:20,834 --> 00:19:23,625
BUT WE STILL DON'T KNOW
WHEN THE NEXT ECLIPSE
IS GONNA HAPPEN.

349
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:25,792
DON'T BE STUPID.
WE'LL FIND OUT LATER.

350
00:19:25,834 --> 00:19:27,583
NO, WE WON'T.
IF WE LEAVE THIS PLACE,

351
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:29,500
WE'LL NEVER GET
THE INFORMATION.

352
00:19:29,542 --> 00:19:32,792
AANG, COME WITH ME
TO THE PLANETARIUM.
I NEED COVER.

353
00:19:32,834 --> 00:19:34,500
KATARA, TAKE MOMO
AND GET OUT OF HERE.

354
00:19:34,542 --> 00:19:35,166
BUT--

355
00:19:35,208 --> 00:19:36,166
Sokka: GO!

356
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,458
HURRY, SOKKA!

357
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,750
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

358
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:53,750
WHAT IS IT NOW?

359
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:04,291
WHO IS THERE?

360
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:13,208
Aang: WHY ARE WE
DOING THIS?

361
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:14,583
BECAUSE IF THIS
CALENDAR CAN TELL US
ABOUT ECLIPSES

362
00:20:14,625 --> 00:20:17,333
IN THE PAST, THEN
MAYBE IT CAN PROJECT

363
00:20:17,375 --> 00:20:18,834
WHEN THE NEXT ONE
WILL BE.

364
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:19,959
YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY
CHECK EVERY SINGLE DATE.

365
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,834
I DON'T HAVE
TO. WE JUST
NEED TO CHECK

366
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:25,125
EVERY DATE BEFORE
SOZEN'S COMET
ARRIVES,

367
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:28,750
BECAUSE AFTER THAT,
WELL, TRY NOT TO
THINK ABOUT THAT.

368
00:20:48,792 --> 00:20:49,667
COME ON, ECLIPSE!

369
00:20:53,583 --> 00:20:55,291
Sokka: THAT'S IT--
THE SOLAR ECLIPSE.

370
00:20:55,333 --> 00:20:57,500
IT'S JUST A FEW
MONTHS AWAY.

371
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,500
GOT IT! NOW LET'S
GET TO BA SING SE.

372
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:21,750
DON'T MAKE ME PUT THIS DOWN.

373
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:34,500
NO! STOP SINKING!

374
00:21:36,959 --> 00:21:41,250
NO!

375
00:21:41,291 --> 00:21:42,291
I'M SORRY, APPA.

376
00:21:46,417 --> 00:21:47,291
[CHATTERING]

377
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,333
[SCREECHING]

378
00:22:01,417 --> 00:22:04,917
AT LEAST I'LL HAVE
ONE SPECIMEN TO ADD
TO MY COLLECTION.

379
00:22:04,959 --> 00:22:05,917
AAH!

380
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:18,875
YOUR WATERBENDING
WON'T DO YOU MUCH
GOOD HERE.

381
00:22:18,917 --> 00:22:22,083
I'VE STUDIED
NORTHERN WATER STYLE,
SOUTHERN WATER STYLE,

382
00:22:22,125 --> 00:22:24,917
EVEN FOGGY SWAMP STYLE.

383
00:22:24,959 --> 00:22:27,709
HYAH!

384
00:22:30,542 --> 00:22:33,667
THAT'S CALLED SOKKA STYLE.
LEARN IT.

385
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:41,333
WAIT! PROFESSOR,
LET'S GO.

386
00:22:41,375 --> 00:22:44,792
I'M NOT LEAVING.
I CAN'T.

387
00:22:44,834 --> 00:22:47,792
I'VE SPENT TOO LONG
TRYING TO FIND
THIS PLACE.

388
00:22:47,834 --> 00:22:49,417
THERE'S NOT
ANOTHER COLLECTION
OF KNOWLEDGE

389
00:22:49,458 --> 00:22:50,917
LIKE THIS ON EARTH.

390
00:22:50,959 --> 00:22:54,041
I COULD SPEND
AN ETERNITY IN HERE.

391
00:22:54,083 --> 00:22:55,375
JUST GO!

392
00:22:55,417 --> 00:22:58,834
[WAN-CHI TONG SCREECHES]

393
00:22:58,875 --> 00:23:02,333
[KIDS SCREAMING]

394
00:23:24,417 --> 00:23:25,667
WE GOT IT.

395
00:23:25,709 --> 00:23:27,333
THERE'S A SOLAR
ECLIPSE COMING.

396
00:23:27,375 --> 00:23:28,709
THE FIRE NATION'S
IN TROUBLE NOW.

397
00:23:32,041 --> 00:23:33,834
WHERE'S APPA?

398
00:23:52,542 --> 00:23:54,750
♪♪
